Jonathan is making a special blend of juice for a picnic with his friends. He mixes apple juice and orange juice in the ratio $\dfrac{3}{2} : 4$. If he uses $2\dfrac{1}{2}$ litres of orange juice, 

\begin{enumerate}
  \item How many litres of apple juice should Jonathan use to maintain the given ratio?
  \item What is the total amount of juice (in litres) Jonathan will have after mixing the apple and orange juices?
\end{enumerate}

